\sum_{k=1}^{m-1}{\frac{1}{\sin^2(\frac{k\pi}{m})}}=\frac{\sum_{k=1}^{m-1}{\prod_{j \not =k}{\sin^2(\frac{j\pi}{m})}}}{\prod_{i=1}^{m-1}{\sin^2(\frac{k\pi}{m})}}=-\frac{b_m}{a_m}
